```class Solution {
    public int minAddToMakeValid(String s) {
        int res = 0, cnt = 0;
        for (char c : s.toCharArray()) {
            if (c == '(') cnt++;
            else if (cnt > 0) cnt--;
            else res++;
        }
        return res + cnt;
    }
}```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: This solution uses a single pass through the string, keeping track of the count of open parentheses and the number of moves required. It increments the result by 1 for each unmatched closing parenthesis and decrements the count for each matched closing parenthesis. The final result is the sum of the moves required and the remaining open parentheses.

